'''Dmitry Itskov''' (Russian: Дмитрий Ицков) is a Russian entrepreneur, billionaire and the founder of ''New Media Stars'', a web-based media company. He has made a reported £1bn from his Moscow-based news publishing company.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Telegraph|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2016/03/13/media-mogul-dmitry-itskov-plans-to-live-forever-by-uploading-his/|accessdate=10 January 2017}}</ref> Itskov is best known for being the founder of the [[2045 Initiative]], which aims to achieve cybernetic [[immortality]] by the year 2045.<ref>{{cite web|last=Alserver|first=Jennifer|title=5 billionaires who want to live forever|url=http://money.cnn.com/gallery/magazines/fortune/2013/04/04/live-forever.fortune/|publisher=CNN}}</ref> Itskov started his foundation in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Independent|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/dmitry-itskov-2045-initiative-immortality-brain-uploading-a6930416.html|accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref>
Itskov said, in a 2016 [[BBC]] ''Horizon'' TV documentary, that the "ultimate goal of [his] plan is to transfer someone’s personality into the new artificial carrier."<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2016/03/13/media-mogul-dmitry-itskov-plans-to-live-forever-by-uploading-his/</ref>
