{{Infobox person | name = Lisa Bettany | image = Lisa Bettany.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1981|11|03}} | birth_place = [[Victoria, British Columbia]], Canada | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Canadian | other_names = | occupation = Photographer, Entrepreneur | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = [[Camera+]] app }}
'''Lisa Bettany''' (born 3 November 1981)<ref>{{cite web|title=It's My Birthday|url=http://mostlylisa.com/blog/its-my-birthday/|publisher=Mostly Lisa|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> is a Canadian technology entrepreneur and photographer. She is a cofounder of the [[iPhone]] camera app [[Camera+]], which had sold over 10 million copies as of 2012.<ref name="Nation's next billionaires">{{cite news|last=Nicholas|first=Sadie|title=Britain's under-30s tipped to be the nation's next billionaires|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/452826/Britain-s-under-30s-tipped-to-be-the-nation-s-next-billionaires|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Daily Express|date=9 January 2014}}</ref>
The daughter of British parents, Bettany grew up in [[Victoria, British Columbia]], where her father was a computer professor.<ref name=Record>{{cite news|last=Barry|first=Maggie|title=Meet the girl who means Scotland's most eligible bachelor is offthemarket.com|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/meet-the-girl-who-means-scotlands-1086134|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Daily Record and Sunday Mail|date=6 November 2011}}</ref><ref name="Alumni mag">{{cite web|last=Chrumka|first=Jennifer|title=university of Victoria Torch magazine|url=http://issuu.com/uvic_torch_alumni_magazine/docs/2012-autumn/22|work=App Snaps|publisher=Issuu.com|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> She was a competitive figure skater from the age of three until a back injury ended her career at 19.<ref name="Record"/> Having grown up around computers, she developed her first blog and her interest in photography while recuperating.<ref name="Record"/> In 2009, Bettany partnered with an international team of six developers to develop Camera+, which launched in June 2010. The app, developed for tap tap tap, generated revenues of almost $2 million within a year for the developer team.<ref name="Apps to riches">{{cite news|last=Resnick|first=Rosalind|title=Camera+: An Apps to Riches Story|url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/219913|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Entrepreneur|date=July 6, 2011}}</ref>
Lisa Bettany was included in the 2014 ''[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]]'' Most Creative People in Business 1000 list.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lisa Bettany, cofounder Camera+|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/person/lisa-bettany|publisher=Fast Company|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' named Bettany as a top female tech entrepreneur in 2012.<ref name=Forbes>{{cite news|title=Women Entrepreneurs Building Killer iPhone Apps|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/women2/2012/09/21/women-entrepreneurs-building-killer-iphone-apps/|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Forbes|date=2012-09-21}}</ref> She has also been featured in ''[[Entrepreneur (magazine)|Entrepreneur]]'',<ref name="Apps to riches"/> ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' magazine,<ref>{{cite news|title=Million Dollar Babes|url=http://www.elle.com/life-love/society-career/successfull-business-women-entrepreneurs-lisa-bettany#slide-5|accessdate=9 March 2014|publisher=Elle}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref name=Bits>{{cite news|last=Chen|first=Brian X.|title=Camera+, a Top-Selling iPhone App, Expands to iPad|url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/09/27/camera-plus-ipad-app/?_php=true&_type=blogs&_r=1|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=New York Times|date=September 27, 2012}}</ref> ''Fast Company Labs<ref name="Fast Co Labs">{{cite news|last=Hayes|first=Tyler|title=8 Master Apple Developers--And They’re All Women|url=http://www.fastcolabs.com/3015220/8-master-apple-developers-and-theyre-all-women#1|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Fast Company Labs|date=2 August 2013}}</ref> and ShutterLove.<ref name=Shutterlove>{{cite news|last=Walsh|first=Brienne|title=How Photography Helped Camera+ Co-Founder Lisa Bettany Get Her Life Back on Track|url=http://www.shutterloveonline.com/photography-tips/sharepublishonline/How-Photography-Help-1656.shtml|accessdate=9 March 2014|newspaper=Shutterlove|date=December 20, 2013}}</ref>
She is on the team at [[MacHeist]] as a producer and has played the characters of Sophia and Amelia. She was formerly a host on Canadian gadget show ''[[GetConnected]]''.<ref name="Apps to riches"/><ref>{{cite web|title=The Team|url=http://www.macheist.com/about|publisher=MacHeist|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interview with Lisa Bettany|url=https://www.dodho.com/interview-lisa-bettany/|website=Dodho Magazine}}</ref>
